Maunie Banking Company, Appellant, v. John Eplin, Appellee.

(Not to be reported in full.)

Abstract of the Decision.Appeal ajstd ebbob, § 1787*—when judgment reversed and cause remanded. Where appellee fails to file a brief, the judgment should he reversed pro forma, under Rule 27, and the cause remanded.Appeal from the Circuit Court of White county; the Hon. Julius C. Keen, Judge, presiding. Heard in this court át the October term, 1916.Reversed pro forma and remanded.Opinion filed April 13, 1917.

Statement of the Case.

Action by Maunie Banking Company, plaintiff, against John Eplin, defendant. From a judgment for defendant, plaintiff appeals.

Noah C. Bainum, for appellant.No appearance for appellee.

See Illinois Notes Digest, Vols. XI to XV, and Cumulative Quarterly, same topic Mid section number.

 Mb. Presiding Justice McBride

delivered the opinion of the court.
